snippet.title: How the Country Reacted over Demonetisation of Rs 500 and Rs 1000 Currency Notes

localized.description:
How the country reacted over demonetisation of Rs 500 and Rs 1000 currency notes. Private hospitals and medical stores are denying to take 500 and 1000 rupee notes. Even common men are struggling to buy their consumable things for basic needs.
Modi government has banned Rs 500 and Rs 1000 currency notes to tackle terrorism, corruption, drug menace and black money.
